       DH_generate_parameters() generates Diffie-Hellman
       parameters that can be shared among a group of users, and
       returns them in a newly allocated DDHH structure. The
       pseudo-random number generator must be seeded prior to
       calling DH_generate_parameters().

       pprriimmee_lleenn is the length in bits of the safe prime to be
       generated.  ggeenneerraattoorr is a small number > 1, typically 2
       or 5.

